  "text": "Node.js implements comprehensive defenses against prototype pollution across its core JavaScript utilities. The primary defense mechanisms are centralized in lib/internal/per_context/primordials.js, which provides safe alternatives to standard JavaScript built-ins.\n\nKey Defense Patterns:\n\n1. **Safe Built-in Collections (lib/internal/per_context/primordials.js)**:\n   - SafeMap, SafeSet, SafeWeakMap, SafeWeakSet: Subclasses of Map, Set, and WeakMap with null prototypes\n   - SafeFinalizationRegistry, SafeWeakRef: Safe versions of FinalizationRegistry and WeakRef\n   - These are created using the makeSafe() function which: (1) sets prototype to null, (2) freezes the prototype and class, (3) copies properties safely using ReflectDefineProperty with __proto__: null descriptors\n\n2. **Safe Iterators (lib/internal/per_context/primordials.js, lines 340-353, 408-431)**:\n   - SafeIterator, SafeArrayIterator, SafeStringIterator: Prevent iterator protocol manipulation\n   - Use ObjectSetPrototypeOf(SafeIterator.prototype, null) to remove prototype chain\n   - Created via createSafeIterator() which captures original iterator behavior\n\n3. **Object.create(null) Patterns**:\n   - lib/internal/worker/io.js (line 115): MessagePortPrototype = ObjectCreate(null, {...})\n   - lib/quic.js (lines 36, 43): Uses ObjectSeal(ObjectCreate(null, {...})) for constants\n   - lib/assert.js (line 110): options = ObjectAssign({ __proto__: null, ... }, options)\n   - Creates null-prototype objects preventing __proto__ pollution attacks\n\n4. **Safe Property Access (ObjectPrototypeHasOwnProperty)**:\n   - lib/buffer.js (line 38, 977): ObjectPrototypeHasOwnProperty from primordials\n   - lib/child_process.js (line 38, 536): Safe environment variable checking\n   - lib/internal/validators.js: Property validation using ObjectPrototypeHasOwnProperty\n   - lib/internal/crypto/util.js, webidl.js: Algorithm and dictionary member validation\n   - Avoids prototype pollution by using uncurried Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty\n\n5. **Null Prototype Assignment (ObjectSetPrototypeOf(obj, null))**:\n   - lib/internal/abort_controller.js (line 443): dependentSignalsToAbort = ObjectSetPrototypeOf([], null)\n   - lib/internal/encoding.js: Property values set to null prototype\n   - lib/internal/bootstrap/realm.js (line): ModuleWrap.prototype set to null\n   - lib/internal/modules/esm/hooks.js: Async hook prototypes set to null\n   - lib/internal/modules/esm/loader.js: ModuleLoader.prototype set to null\n   - lib/internal/modules/esm/module_job.js: ModuleJobBase.prototype set to null\n   - lib/internal/util/inspect.js (line): Format return values set to null prototype\n   - Prevents prototype chain traversal attacks\n\n6. **Safe Merge/Assign Patterns**:\n   - lib/assert.js: ObjectAssign({ __proto__: null, ... }, userOptions)\n   - lib/internal/http2/core.js (lines 2371, 2913, 3181): Headers = ObjectAssign({ __proto__: null }, headers)\n   - lib/internal/http2/util.js (line 712): headersObject = ObjectAssign({ __proto__: null }, headers)\n   - lib/internal/modules/esm/translators.js (line 562): wrappedModule = ObjectAssign({ __proto__: null }, imports)\n   - lib/internal/util/inspect.js (line 506): inspect.styles = ObjectAssign({ __proto__: null }, {...})\n   - Ensures merged objects cannot be polluted via __proto__\n\n7. **Safe Descriptor Creation (copyPropsRenamed)**:\n   - lib/internal/per_context/primordials.js (lines 75-95, 97-113): Uses ReflectDefineProperty with { __proto__: null, ...desc } to copy property descriptors safely\n   - Prevents descriptor objects from being polluted\n\n8. **Freezing Safe Objects**:\n   - lib/internal/per_context/primordials.js (line 397-399): ObjectFreeze on safe prototypes and classes\n   - lib/internal/per_context/primordials.js (line 746): ObjectSetPrototypeOf(primordials, null) followed by freeze\n   - lib/internal/streams/fast-utf8-stream.js: const kNullPrototype = { __proto__: null }\n\n9. **Wide Usage of Safe Collections**:\n   - 94 files use SafeMap/SafeSet including: abort_controller, async_context_frame, diagnostics_channel, event_target, freeze_intrinsics, mime, trace_events_async_hooks, tty, url, util, webidl, worker modules\n   - lib/domain.js: vmPromises = new SafeWeakMap(), pairing = new SafeMap()\n   - lib/_http_outgoing.js: unique = new SafeSet()\n\n10. **Error Serialization Safety (lib/internal/error_serdes.js)**:\n    - Uses ObjectCreate and ObjectAssign with null prototypes for error properties\n    - Prevents error object property pollution\n\nThese defenses work in concert: (1) SafeMap/SafeSet prevent collection prototype pollution, (2) ObjectPrototypeHasOwnProperty checks prevent property enumeration attacks, (3) null-prototype objects prevent __proto__ pollution, (4) ObjectSetPrototypeOf(null) prevents prototype chain attacks, and (5) safe merge patterns ensure incoming data cannot pollute safe objects. Together, these patterns form a comprehensive defense-in-depth strategy protecting Node.js core utilities from prototype pollution attacks."
